RFH Community,

We invite you to help us plan for our future by participating in our outreach activities scheduled for early February. Community Outreach conversations are scheduled for Monday, February 3, 2020 from 3:45 - 4:45 and on Thursday, February 6, 2020 in the RFH High School Library. There are three main topics we will be discussing:
-Athletics and Activities
-Curriculum and College Planning
-Communication

If you would like to attend either of these sessions, please RSVP at this link: shorturl.at/mwzQ6

You are also encouraged to share your thoughts by completing this survey. The survey questions focus on communication; there are places to leave comments about any topic within the survey. Click on the appropriate link below:

Survey for Parents: http://bit.ly/30299wu

Survey for Community Members: http://bit.ly/300DThq

Thank you for your participation!

post_text: On Friday, December 6th, nineteen students from the Science National Honor Society and Scientific Frontier Club were able to participate in NJIT's Engineering Career Day. As they toured the campus, they were given background information on various types of engineering fields. They were able to try their hand at using a bridge-building program to efficiently create a bridge, sit in one of NJIT's custom-built go-carts, and meet with faculty and staff from various engineering disciplines.

post_text: The Marching Bulldogs are having a great season! On Saturday, September 14th, the Bulldogs competed at Brick Memorial HS in the Mustang Roundup and placed 1st in Group 1A. They followed that up with a 2nd place finish in USBands Group 1A at the Jackson Jaguar Showcase of Champions.

post_text: The Fair Haven First Floors House Tour is THIS WEEK! Tickets are on sale NOW. Please visit www.fairhavenpta.com to purchase tickets for $65. Check out the website www.fairhavenfirstfloors.com for all the details. Tickets include a self-guided tour of eight beautiful Fair Haven homes. Each home will offer food from local restaurants and have a mix of designers, builders, home organizers, and home-related services all on hand to meet and see their work up close! You don't want to miss this event Thursday, May 16th from 9:30 am-2:00 pm. All proceeds go to the Fair Haven PTA to help fund the programs that make our schools so special.

post_text: What does “Tax Neutral” mean? For RFH’s bond referendum, it means taxpayers have been accustomed to making payments on a bond that is almost complete, so the Oct. 2 proposal is timed to continue what is already in place.
